    "# üèÜ Module 14: ADAS Capstone Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This is your final project. You will design, implement, and document your own custom Advanced Driver Assistance System feature, integrating all the skills you have learned throughout this course."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 1: Your Mission\n",
    "\n",
    "Your mission is to act as an automotive engineer. Identify a safety challenge and build a functional ADAS feature to address it. You will use the VESC, the AI Camera, and the buzzer to create a complete, integrated system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 2: Project Options\n",
    "\n",
    "Choose one of the following advanced projects, or propose your own custom idea to your instructor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Option A: Enhanced FCW with Predictive Alerts\n",
    "**Challenge:** The Forward Collision Warning system from Module 13 is purely reactive. It only knows an object's current position. An *enhanced* system would predict where an object is *going*.\n",
    "**Implementation:**\n",
    "1. Track the center point of a detected 'person' over several frames.\n",
    "2. Calculate the object's velocity (change in position over time).\n",
    "3. Predict the object's future position.\n",
    "4. Issue an earlier, 'predictive' warning if the object's predicted path will intersect with your vehicle's path."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Option B: Multi-Object Threat Assessment\n",
    "**Challenge:** A real road has many objects. Your system needs to decide which one is the most immediate threat.\n",
    "**Implementation:**\n",
    "1. In your detection loop, iterate through *all* detected objects (people, cars, etc.).\n",
    "2. For each object, calculate a 'threat score' based on a formula you design. The score should consider:\n",
    "   - **Time-to-Collision (TTC):** Lower TTC = higher threat.\n",
    "   - **Confidence:** Higher confidence = higher threat.\n",
    "   - **Size (Bounding Box Area):** Larger area (closer object) = higher threat.\n",
    "3. Display a dashboard that lists all detected objects, but only issue an alert for the object with the highest threat score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Option C: Speed Limit Zone Enforcement\n",
    "**Challenge:** Build a system that can recognize a specific visual marker (like a stop sign, or even a custom QR code you print out) and suggest a speed reduction.\n",
    "**Implementation:**\n",
    "1. Train your system to recognize the 'stop sign' label from the COCO dataset.\n",
    "2. Create a 'speed zone' state variable in your code.\n",
    "3. When a stop sign is detected with high confidence, enter the 'speed zone' state.\n",
    "4. While in this state, if the vehicle's RPM is above a certain low threshold (e.g., 500 RPM), issue a continuous, gentle warning beep.\n",
    "5. Exit the 'speed zone' state after a set time (e.g., 10 seconds)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Option D: Custom ADAS Feature\n",
    "**Challenge:** Propose your own idea! It must meet the project requirements below. Discuss with your instructor before starting.\n",
    "**Ideas:** Lane Departure Warning (using image processing to find lines), a "smart brake light" that flashes the buzzer when you brake hard, etc."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 3: Project Requirements & Rubric\n",
    "Your final project will be evaluated based on the following criteria."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Requirements Checklist:\n",
    "- [ ] Must be a complete ADAS feature (not just detection).\n",
    "- [ ] Must use data from **both** the AI Camera and the VESC motor controller.\n",
    "- [ ] Must include multi-level alerts or responses (e.g., different beeps for different danger levels).\n",
    "- [ ] Must handle edge cases gracefully (e.g., what happens if no object is detected?).\n",
    "- [ ] Must include a real-time status dashboard that explains what the system is 'thinking'.\n",
    "- [ ] Must include documentation (in markdown cells) explaining your algorithm with a flowchart."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Evaluation Rubric\n",
    "| Criteria                   | Points | Description                                         |\n",
    "|----------------------------|--------|-----------------------------------------------------|\n",
    "| ADAS Authenticity          | 25     | Feature resembles a real, useful automotive ADAS.     |\n",
    "| Technical Implementation   | 25     | All components work correctly without errors.       |\n",
    "| Innovation                 | 20     | Creative approach or novel improvements.            |\n",
    "| Edge Case Handling         | 15     | System handles unusual situations gracefully.       |\n",
    "| Documentation & Presentation| 15     | Clear explanation, professional presentation.       |"
   ]
  },
  {
